The paper focuses on pruning techniques for deep neural networks (DNN) to achieve acceleration on mobile devices, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) research. The paper also mentions the use of compiler optimization for efficient DNN execution, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
